account(address,bytes32,uint256,address,.details: Returns the computed token bound account address for a non-fungible token.

returns._0: The address of the token bound account

createAccount(address,bytes32,uint256,ad.details: Creates a token bound account for a non-fungible token. If account has already been created, returns the account address without calling create2. Emits ERC6551AccountCreated event.

returns.result: The address of the token bound account

returns._0: bool Whether the spender is approved or the owner of the tokenId.

params.tokenId: The NFT token ID to approve.

params.approved: Whether to approve or revoke approval from the operator.
params.owner: The owner to set operator approvals for.

royaltyInfo(uint256,uint256).details: Returns how much royalty is owed and to whom, based on a sale price that may be denominated in any unit of exchange. The royalty amount is denominated and should be paid in that same unit of exchange.

returns.output: The tokenURI of the dotAgency which is a JSON string.

params.extraData: The extra data of the tokenURIEngine.render function.
params.result: The result of the gateway.getSignedRender function.

getDomainSeparator().notice: Returns the domain separator for this NFT contract.

isAuthorized(address,uint256).notice: Checks whether a given spender is approved to spend a given tokenId, or is the owner of the tokenId.

nextTokenId().notice: Returns the next tokenId that will be minted.

permit(address,uint256,(uint8,bytes32,by.notice: Implementation of an EIP-712 permit function for an ERC-721 NFT. We don't need to check if the tokenId exists, since the function calls ownerOf(tokenId), which reverts if the tokenId does not exist.

permitForAll(address,address,bool,(uint8.notice: Implementation of an EIP-712 permit-style function for ERC-721 operator approvals. Allows an operator address to control all NFTs a given owner owns.
